replies.body:
A pity, to be sure. I am suspect they intended it to sell the whole "incomprehensible, incredibly ancient, celestial being."

Personally, I would have preferred understandable speech, something to give him a bit of character rather than solely embodying his purpose on the cosmic scale. A similar demeanor to Braum, but far more mischievous, and of course a thoughtful hint of shrouded wisdom, like a grandpa that tries to impart sage advice through cheesy metaphors so he can laugh about it while you try to wrap your head around the meaning.

Perhaps he could have had a few poignant lines as well, recounting tales he once witnessed in person and the people who have long since passed on.

"I knew your forebears. The weight of their legacy is great." {{champion:59}}
"The stars were in your eyes once, no more." {{champion:127}}
"My, but the apple does not fall far from the tree." {{champion:22}} 
"You cannot hear them, but the stars still sing your praises." {{champion:16}}

Also, Riot really missed out on his joke:

"Stay a while and listen!"
